<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>EJS Concepts</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <%- include("partials/header") %>

    <div class="container center-content">
      <h1>EJS (Embedded JavaScript)</h1>

      <p class="desc">
        EJS is a templating engine used in Node.js to create dynamic HTML pages.
        It allows you to embed JavaScript directly inside HTML.
      </p>

      <br />

      <h2>Why Use EJS?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>✔ Helps create dynamic web pages</li>
        <li>✔ Easy to integrate with Express.js</li>
        <li>✔ Allows reuse using partials (header/footer)</li>
        <li>✔ Simple syntax (HTML + JavaScript)</li>
      </ul>

      <br />
      <br />

      <h2>Important EJS Concepts</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>&lt;%= %&gt;</strong> → Output data (escaped, safe)</li>
        <li><strong>&lt;%- %&gt;</strong> → Output raw HTML (unescaped)</li>
        <li>
          <strong>&lt;% %&gt;</strong> → JavaScript logic (loops, conditions)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Partials</strong> → Reusable components like header & footer
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Includes</strong> → Use <code>&lt;%- include() %&gt;</code> to
          reuse files
        </li>
      </ul>

      <br />
      <br />

      <h2>Example Page</h2>
      <p>👉 <a href="/users">View Users Example</a></p>
    </div>

    <%- include("partials/footer") %>
  </body>
</html>
